### C3: Admin Registration Endpoint is Publicly Accessible

> **What:** [`admin.routes.js:48`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/routes/admin.routes.js#L48) exposes `POST /api/admin/register` without any authentication or authorization.
>
> **Why it matters:** Anyone on the internet can create admin accounts, gaining access to all admin-protected functionality: team approvals, score manipulation, judge management, player management, and financial data.
>
> **Where:** [`admin.routes.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/routes/admin.routes.js) lines 47-48.

**Current code:**
```javascript
router.post('/register', adminController.registerAdmin);
```

**Fix — require super-admin authentication:**
```javascript
router.post(
  '/register',
  authMiddleware,
  requireSuperAdmin,
  adminValidator.registerAdmin(), // add validation
  handleValidationErrors,
  adminController.registerAdmin
);
```

> Alternatively, remove the public endpoint entirely and only allow admin creation through the existing `scripts/createAdmin.js` CLI tool.

