### H1: In-Memory Token Invalidation Won't Survive Restarts or Scale

> **What:** [`token-invalidation.util.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/utils/security/token-invalidation.util.js) uses `Map()` objects (`adminAssignmentChanges`, `logoutTimestamps`) to track token invalidation.
>
> **Why it matters:** Server restart wipes all invalidation records — all previously logged-out tokens become valid again. In a multi-instance deployment (e.g., Render auto-scaling), invalidation on one instance doesn't affect others. The file itself has a comment acknowledging this ("replace with Redis").
>
> **Where:** [`token-invalidation.util.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/utils/security/token-invalidation.util.js) lines 12-15.
>
> **Fix:**
> - **Short term:** Accept the limitation but set JWT expiry to a shorter window (e.g., 1h instead of 24h) to reduce the exposure window.
> - **Long term:** Implement Redis-backed invalidation or switch to a refresh-token rotation scheme with short-lived access tokens (5-15 min).

