### H4: Duplicate CORS Configuration — `server.js` vs `security.middleware.js`

> **What:** CORS is configured in two places: [`server.js:43-89`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/server.js#L43-L89) (inline with a manual additional headers middleware) and [`security.middleware.js:120-171`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/middleware/security.middleware.js#L120-L171) (properly abstracted `createCorsMiddleware`).
>
> **Why it matters:** The `server.js` version is applied AND then a second middleware manually sets Access-Control headers again (lines 80-89). This is redundant and confusing — changing one without the other will cause subtle CORS bugs. The `security.middleware.js` version is better but unused in the main entry.
>
> **Where:** [`server.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/server.js) lines 42-89.
>
> **Fix:** Remove inline CORS from `server.js` and use the abstracted middleware from `security.middleware.js`:
```javascript
// server.js — replace lines 42-89 with:
const { createCorsMiddleware } = require('./src/middleware/security.middleware');
app.use(createCorsMiddleware(container));
```

