### M4: Judge Model Has No `comparePassword` Method

> **What:** The Player, Coach, and Admin models all define a `comparePassword` method. The [`Judge`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/models/Judge.js) model does not, despite having a password field and pre-save hashing.
>
> **Why it matters:** [`authentication.service.js:560-562`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/services/auth/authentication.service.js#L560-L562) tries `user.comparePassword()` first and falls back to `bcrypt.compare()`. When the `findById` in auth middleware uses `.lean()` (returning a plain object), neither approach works correctly because `.lean()` strips methods AND the password field may not be selected.
>
> **Where:** [`Judge.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/models/Judge.js).
>
> **Fix:** Add `comparePassword` to the Judge model:
```javascript
judgeSchema.methods.comparePassword = async function(candidatePassword) {
  return await bcrypt.compare(candidatePassword, this.password);
};
```

