### M5: OTP Not Cleared After Successful Password Reset

> **What:** In [`authentication.service.js:291-305`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/services/auth/authentication.service.js#L291-L305), after a successful OTP verification and password update, the `resetPasswordToken` is set to `null` as part of the update — but the `otpService.clearOTP()` method is never called. More importantly, the OTP is verified but can potentially be reused in the same window before the update completes.
>
> **Why it matters:** A timing attack could allow the same OTP to be used in parallel requests.
>
> **Where:** [`authentication.service.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/services/auth/authentication.service.js) — `resetPasswordWithOTP` method.
>
> **Fix:** Use an atomic `findOneAndUpdate` with the OTP as a query condition to guarantee single-use:
```javascript
const result = await repository.model.findOneAndUpdate(
  { _id: user._id, resetPasswordToken: otp },
  { password: hashedPassword, resetPasswordToken: null, resetPasswordExpires: null },
  { new: true }
);
if (!result) throw new ValidationError('Invalid or expired OTP');
```

