### M6: Socket Authentication Doesn't Check Token Invalidation

> **What:** [`socket.manager.js:80-120`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/socket/socket.manager.js#L80-L120) verifies the JWT token but does not check `isTokenLoggedOut()` like the HTTP auth middleware does.
>
> **Why it matters:** A user who logs out can still maintain an active socket connection and receive real-time scoring updates. This is inconsistent with the HTTP layer.
>
> **Where:** [`socket.manager.js`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/socket/socket.manager.js) — `createAuthMiddleware` method.
>
> **Fix:** Add the same check:
```javascript
const { isTokenLoggedOut } = require('../utils/security/token-invalidation.util');

// After verifyToken:
if (isTokenLoggedOut(String(decoded.userId), decoded.iat)) {
  return next(new Error('Session ended. Please log in again.'));
}
```

