### L4: `getRepositoryByType` Duplicated Across Services

[`authentication.service.js:581-594`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/services/auth/authentication.service.js#L581-L594) and [`otp.service.js:203-213`](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Server/src/services/auth/otp.service.js#L203-L213) both have identical `getRepositoryByType` switch statements. The OTP service version is missing `'judge'`.

**Fix:** Create a shared `UserRepositoryResolver` utility or inject a pre-built Map:
```javascript
// utils/user-repository-resolver.js
class UserRepositoryResolver {
  constructor(repos) {
    this.repos = new Map(Object.entries(repos));
  }
  resolve(userType) {
    const repo = this.repos.get(userType.toLowerCase());
    if (!repo) throw new Error(`Invalid user type: ${userType}`);
    return repo;
  }
}
```

