## Summary

The codebase is in **good shape architecturally** — the refactoring towards DI/service/repository layers was done thoughtfully. The **three critical issues** (leaked credentials, weak OTP, open admin registration) need immediate attention. The high-priority items (role confusion, architecture bypass, duplicate config) should be addressed within the current sprint. The long-term items (Redis, refresh tokens, audit logging) are investments that will pay off as the platform scales.
